# Nava project rules

## FIRST THING: Read the docs before doing ANYTHING
**Always check the relevant docs first.** Skipping this leads to wrong behavior (e.g. overlap bugs, scan flow going to categories instead of confirm). When starting a session or implementing a feature:
1. **Read** `PROJECT_STATUS.md` — full context, vision, what's built, changelog, **which AI is used where** (chat = Groq, scan = Groq Llama 4 Scout via ai-scan, same key).
2. For UI/platform work: read `docs/DESKTOP_MOBILE_UX.md` and `src-tauri/tauri.conf.json` (e.g. `withGlobalTauri: true` is CRITICAL for desktop).
3. For roadmap/priorities: `COMPETITOR_ANALYSIS.md`, `docs/ROADMAP.md`.
4. For desktop build/release: `docs/TAURI_UPDATES.md`.
Then implement so behavior matches the docs (e.g. Add Item: camera-first → AI scan → **Confirm & track** screen with doc details → Track it or Edit details; never skip confirm and jump to category picker when we have extraction).

## Stack
- **Frontend:** React + Vite, JSX (not TSX)
- **Backend:** Supabase (Postgres, Edge Functions in Deno/TypeScript, Auth)
- **Mobile:** Capacitor (Android/iOS)
- **Desktop:** Tauri 2 (macOS/Windows/Linux)
- **AI:** Multi-provider BYOK (Groq free, OpenAI, Claude, Gemini). Auto-detected from key prefix. Server fallback: GROQ_API_KEY.

## Key architecture
- **Local-first:** compliance_items stored in IndexedDB, synced encrypted to Supabase
- **Platform detection:** `window.__TAURI__` for desktop (requires `withGlobalTauri: true`), `Capacitor.getPlatform()` for mobile
- **E2E encryption:** Email users = password (PBKDF2); OAuth users = auto-generated key
- **Camera-first Add Item:** AI auto-detects document type from photo (AUTO_DETECT_PROMPT)

## Git & docs
- Commit after each logical change. Do not batch unrelated edits into one commit. Use descriptive commit messages explaining the "why".
- **PROJECT_STATUS.md:** Update when adding features or completing work. Add a changelog entry and refresh the Updated date. Keep Recent and Codebase refactor sections accurate.

## Supabase
- Migrations go in `supabase/migrations/` (currently up to 029)
- Run `supabase db push` when adding/changing migrations
- Edge function secrets: `FROM_EMAIL`, `APP_URL`, `RESEND_API_KEY`, `VAPID_KEYS_JSON`; optional `GROQ_API_KEY` for ai-scan if not using user's key.

## Domain & email
- `vicomnava.com` verified with Resend. Emails from `noreply@vicomnava.com`
- Supabase secrets `FROM_EMAIL` and `APP_URL` must be set

## Desktop releases (Tauri)
- Use `npm run release -- <version>`. Signing key at `~/.tauri/nava.key` — never commit
- App icon uses **light (cream bubble)** logo: `npx tauri icon public/nava-logo-light.png`
- GitHub Secrets `TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY` and `TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD` enable CI signed builds

## Components (always follow)
- **Break everything down into components.** Do not leave large inline JSX blocks in pages. Extract modals, multi-element UI, and repeated patterns into named components in `src/components/`.
- Keep components small and single-purpose. Avoid files >300 lines. If a page or component grows, extract sub-components (e.g. modal content → `XxxModal.jsx`, section → `XxxSection.jsx`).
- Category emojis: use `EMPTY_EMOJIS` from `src/components/dashboard/constants.js` — do NOT create local copies.
- Feature folders: `addItem/`, `dashboard/`, `dispute/`, `documents/`, `settings/`, `welcomeGuide/`, `auth/`, `scanUpload/`, `emailSuggestions/`, `chat/`. Shared UI (modals, prompts) live in `components/modals/` or `components/common/`.

## CSS
- All styles in `src/index.css` with CSS custom properties
- Mobile breakpoint: `max-width: 640px`
- Desktop hover-reveal on item cards; mobile swipe actions
- 44px minimum touch targets on mobile

## Testing
- See `docs/TESTING.md` for QA checklist
- Build: `npm run build` must pass
- Lint: `npx eslint .` — 0 errors allowed (3 pre-existing warnings OK)

## What NOT to do
- Never remove `withGlobalTauri: true` from tauri.conf.json
- Never add polling/detection hacks for `window.__TAURI__` — it's available synchronously
- Never put download links in the desktop/mobile app
- Never commit `.env`, `~/.tauri/nava.key`, or other secrets
